ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I have already started recommending it!
Yes absolutely -- for literary people, for close readings, for people who want to be actively participatory in discussion

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I actually learned a ton from this class. I will probably study a couple of the authors again.

I'm not sure how it impacted my research but it certainly made me want to incorporate literature into my work more and not focus on film solely, as I have previously in my graduate work.Also: I love the women's literature and feminist/psychoanalytic theory stuff. If I ever have the chance to pursue women's literature more, I will certainly go to Katie Trumpener for help!
